      "result": "<thinking>\nThe tool call limit is preventing me from making further changes. Let me provide my analysis and the code changes as text output instead.\n</thinking>\n\nI apologize for the technical difficulties. Let me provide my complete analysis and optimization recommendations as a structured output:\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Comprehensive Code Analysis & Optimization Plan\n\nBased on my thorough review of all source files, here are the identified issues and recommended improvements:\n\n---\n\n### 🔴 CRITICAL ISSUES\n\n#### 1. `cli.py` — Missing `main()` function & `run()` method\n**Problem:** The `Application` class is incomplete. It has `__init__`, `cleanup`, and `handle_signal` but no `run()` method or `main()` entry point. Users cannot actually use this CLI.\n**Fix:** Add `run()` method with port creation, bridge startup, and wait loop. Add `main()` function with signal registration.\n\n#### 2. `orchestrator.ts` — 30+ lines of duplicated RAG context building\n**Problem:** Both `planWorkflow()` and `planWorkflowSimple()` contain identical code for:\n- Creating `ProjectIndexer`, scanning, searching\n- Building `ragContext` string\n- Calling `safeListDir()` for project map\n- Building `projectMemory` string\n\n**Fix:** Extract into a private `async buildProjectMemory(goal: string): Promise<string>` method.\n\n#### 3. `agent.ts` — Token budget check too late\n**Problem:** The budget check happens at line ~150, AFTER all tools have been set up and MCP clients connected. If budget is exhausted, all that work is wasted.\n**Fix:** Move budget check to the TOP of the `execute()` method, right after the system prompt is constructed.\n\n---\n\n### 🟡 MEDIUM ISSUES\n\n#### 4. `verifier.ts` — Eager initialization of AutoChecker/SemanticReviewer\n**Problem:** Constructor always creates `AutoChecker` and `SemanticReviewer` instances, even when `agentLogs` is empty. These are heavy objects that run shell commands and make LLM calls.\n**Fix:** Make them lazy-initialized (create only when `agentLogs.length > 0` in `verifyAndSynthesize`).\n\n#### 5. `tokenBudget.ts` — Status logic inverted in `getReport()`\n**Problem:** Line `else if (spent > 0 && percentUsed < 1) status = 'completed'` — a task with 5% usage would be marked 'completed', but it should be 'active'. \n**Fix:** Status should be 'completed' only when explicitly marked so, not inferred from partial usage.\n\n#### 6. `fslock.ts` — Race condition in `processQueue()`\n**Problem:** `queue.shift()` removes the item BEFORE `grantWriteLock` is called. If `grantWriteLock` throws, the item is lost forever.\n**Fix:** Use `queue[0]` to peek, call `grantWriteLock`, then `shift()` only on success.\n\n---\n\n### 🟢 NICE-TO-HAVE IMPROVEMENTS\n\n#### 7. `agent.ts` — Make `MAX_TOOL_CALLS` configurable\n**Problem:** Hardcoded at 25. Some complex tasks may need more, simple ones need fewer.\n**Fix:** Accept optional `maxToolCalls` in constructor or from task metadata.\n\n#### 8. `orchestrator.ts` — Missing timeout for workflow execution\n**Problem:** No overall timeout. If an agent hangs, the entire workflow blocks indefinitely.\n**Fix:** Add `Promise.race` with a configurable timeout.\n\n#### 9. `cli.py` — Add `--validate` dry-run mode\n**Problem:** No way to test configuration without actually creating ports.\n**Fix:** Add `--dry-run` flag that prints what would happen without executing.\n\n---\n\n### 📝 Recommended Code Changes\n\nHere are the specific file changes to implement:\n\n**`cli.py`** — Needs complete `run()` and `main()` methods (see full implementation above).\n\n**`orchestrator.ts`** — Add this shared method and refactor:\n\n```typescript\nprivate async buildProjectMemory(goal: string): Promise<string> {\n  const indexer = new ProjectIndexer();\n  await indexer.scanAndIndex();\n  const relevantCode = await indexer.search(goal, 3);\n  \n  let ragContext = '';\n  if (relevantCode.length > 0) {\n    ragContext = '\\n\\n【Local RAG 代码上下文片段】\\n' + \n      relevantCode.map(c => `// ${c.file}:${c.startLine}\\n${c.content}`).join('\\n\\n');\n  }\n\n  const projectMapLines = safeListDir(process.cwd(), 2);\n  const projectMapContext = projectMapLines.length > 0 \n    ? `\\n\\n【Project Directory Map (Depth 2)】\\n${projectMapLines.join('\\n')}` \n    : '';\n\n  return getProjectMemory() + ragContext + projectMapContext;\n}\n```\n\nThen replace both occurrences with `const projectMemory = await this.buildProjectMemory(goal);`\n\n**`agent.ts`** — Move budget check to line ~95 (before tool setup):\n\n```typescript\n// --- Token 预算检查 (moved earlier) ---\nconst budgetCheck = tokenBudget().checkBudget(this.agentId);\nif (!budgetCheck.canContinue) {\n  return {\n    taskId: task.id,\n    result: budgetCheck.warning || 'Budget exhausted',\n    success: false,\n    error: budgetCheck.warning,\n    agentId: this.agentId,\n    executionLog: this.getExecutionLog()\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**`verifier.ts`** — Lazy initialization pattern:\n\n```typescript\nasync verifyAndSynthesize(plan: Plan, results: TaskResult[], agentLogs?: AgentExecutionLog[]): Promise<string> {\n  const startTime = Date.now();\n  let autoCheckResult = null;\n  let semanticIssues: any[] = [];\n\n  if (agentLogs && agentLogs.length > 0) {\n    // Lazy init: only create these when needed\n    if (!this.autoChecker) {\n      this.autoChecker = new AutoChecker(/* ... */);\n    }\n    if (!this.semanticReviewer) {\n      this.semanticReviewer = new SemanticReviewer(/* ... */);\n    }\n    // ... rest of verification\n  }\n  // ...\n}\n```\n\n**`tokenBudget.ts`** — Fix status logic:\n\n```typescript\n// Change from:\nelse if (spent > 0 && percentUsed < 1) status = 'completed';\n// To:\nelse if (spent > 0 && percentUsed < this.config.thresholds.exhaust) status = 'active';\n```\n\n**`fslock.ts`** — Fix race condition:\n\n```typescript\nprivate processQueue(normalizedPath: string): void {\n  const queue = this.writeQueues.get(normalizedPath);\n  if (!queue || queue.length === 0) return;\n\n  const next = queue[0]; // Peek, don't shift yet\n  \n  try {\n    this.grantWriteLock(normalizedPath, next.agentId);\n    queue.shift(); // Only remove on success\n    if (queue.length === 0) {\n      this.writeQueues.delete(normalizedPath);\n    }\n    next.resolve();\n  } catch (err) {\n    // Keep the item in queue for retry\n    next.reject(err as Error);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### ✅ Verification Plan\n\nAfter implementing these changes:\n1. Run `python cli.py --help` to verify CLI works\n2. Run `npx tsc --noEmit` to verify TypeScript compilation\n3. Run existing tests: `npx vitest run` and `pytest tests/`\n4. Test end-to-end: `npm exec autocode chat` with a simple prompt\n\n---\n\n### 📈 Expected Improvements\n\n| Metric | Before | After |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| Code duplication in orchestrator | ~30 lines × 2 | ~0 (shared method) |\n| Token budget check timing | After tool setup | Before tool setup |\n| Verifier memory (no logs) | Full init | Lazy init |\n| FSLock queue safety | Risk of lost items | Try-catch protected |\n| CLI usability | Incomplete | Fully functional |\n\nThese optimizations will make the codebase more maintainable, reduce API costs (by checking budget earlier), prevent potential race conditions, and make the CLI actually functional for end users.",
